Bring a large #pot of salted water to a boil. Once boiling, add @Cheese Tortelloni{9%ounce} and reduce heat to a simmer. Cook, stirring occasionally, until tortelloni are al dente and floating to the top, ~{3-5%minutes}. Drain.

Heat a medium pan over medium-high heat. Add @Marinara Cup{14%ounce} and bring to a low simmer. Gently stir in drained tortelloni until coated.

Divide between #bowls{} and serve.

> Recipe suggestion (additional ingredients not included): Heat a drizzle of oil in a medium pan over medium high heat. Add @garlic{2%cloves}(thinly sliced) and a pinch of @chili flakes{}; cook until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}. Pour in marinara and bring to a simmer, then gently stir in drained tortelloni until coated. Divide between bowls and sprinkle with @Parmesan{}. Top with @?fresh basil{}(chopped) or @?parsley{}(chopped).